    <h1>Simple Checkout Example</h1>
      <p>
      This example demonstrates how the checkout SDK can be integrated easily in
      a Web application. 
      </p>
      
      <p>
      The sample project provided simulates the control flow and the different
      types of messages that are sent back and forth between the client and the
      merchant after the buyer clicks on the Google Checkout button as described
      on the <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/checkout/developer/index.html">
        Google Checkout API
      </a> page.
      </p>
      
      <p>
      While trying out the samples project, you may be asked to enter a credit card
      number on Google Checkout's Sandbox testing environment.  Simply use one of 
      the provided credit card numbers found at the 
      <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/checkout/developer/index.html#integration_overview">
        Integration Overview
      </a> section of the Google Checkout API page.
      </p>
